text: Also known as Seshat, Sefkhet-Abwy was the goddess of writing and libraries. In many depictions she is shown as the daughter of Thoth and Maa't. Her sacred symbols were leopard skin, the tablet, the stylus and the seven pronged star on her headdress. More information available on the Seshat page. Category:Egyptian gods and goddesses
title: Sefkhet-Abwy
